1. uberae . . . videmus: ‘ our thoughts are free and gaze in imagination at what they wish, thus enabling us to see what we do not behold.' The topic, sc. the comparison of things which we do not see, with things which we do, is frequent in Cicero, e.g. Deiot. 40 id animo contemplare, quod oculis non potes: Fam. v. 17. 4 nec minus nostra sunt, quae animo complectimur, quam quae oculis intuemur.
